Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at a private residence in Chicago, Illinois. She thanked her friends and supporters for their continuous support throughout her career. Harris reflected on the accomplishments of the 2020 election, including record voter turnout and the passage of transformative legislation such as the infrastructure bill and healthcare reforms. She emphasized the need to continue the work and win the House and Senate in order to protect women's reproductive rights, pass voting rights legislation, and implement gun safety laws. Harris highlighted the importance of democracy and the United States' role as a global leader. She urged the audience to recognize the impact their work has on people both in America and around the world.